# Local AI Stack — environment variables for API keys and secrets.
#
# Usage:
#   1. Copy this file to `.env.local` (already gitignored) AND load the values
#      into your shell / user profile so the Open WebUI tools (which run inside
#      `pipelines` container or as user functions) can read them at startup.
#   2. On Windows, run `scripts/set-env-vars.ps1 -EnvFile .env.local` from an
#      elevated PowerShell to persist these as User env vars. Alternatively,
#      `docker compose --env-file .env.local up -d` will substitute values in
#      `docker-compose.yml` without storing them in the registry.
#   3. Leave any key blank if you don't use that tool — each tool falls back
#      gracefully when its key is empty.
#
# Never commit `.env.local` or a filled-out copy of this file. Rotate any key
# that ends up in git history.

# ── Open WebUI / stack internals ────────────────────────────────────────────
PIPELINES_API_KEY=
JUPYTER_TOKEN=local-ai-stack-token
OPENAI_API_KEYS=lmstudio;0p3n-w3bu!

